race.comment: Tricky little contest with plenty of chances. BONJOUR MADAME (4) has struggled at her two runs back on the provincial circuit, and hopefully the blinkers can switch her on. Maps well and racing like this trip will suit. Each way. HIBIKI HARMONY (2) ran her rivals ragged when eased down late for a slick victory over this track and trip from the wide gate. Will take control from the low draw and prove hard to get past. TILLSTROM (5) Vancouver gelding who looked even better at his second race start when demolishing a handy field over the 1450m here. Undefeated and can raise the bar again. LAIZABOUT (3) returned in good order and just needs a bit of luck from the draw to take a hand in the finish.
